[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"initial_plan View Reasoning before tools: To build a credible book adapted to Enneagram personalities from the linked YouTube video, I need the video’s transcript and core frameworks to transform them (not copy) into a structured book. I also need authoritative Enneagram references to correctly tailor messaging, pain points, and growth paths for each of the nine types, plus publishing/monetization best practices to produce a tactical SOP. I will 1) fetch and analyze the YouTube transcript, 2) research Enneagram foundations, 3) research KDP/Gumroad and funnel best practices, then synthesize into a book blueprint, production SOP tables with inputs/outputs, and charts. Now pulling the transcript and references. Using Tool | Understand Videos BUiVWGs0cIY View Reasoning before tools: I need reputable references for Enneagram fundamentals (9 types, motivations, growth/stress), Gardner’s Multiple Intelligences (to ground the mapping), and publishing/monetization best practices (KDP, Gumroad, launch). I’ll run parallel searches, then open the most authoritative sources to cite accurately. Using Tool | Parallel Search Enneagram nine types overview Riso Hudson site The Enneagram Institute type descriptions core motivations Narrative Enneagram growth and stress lines explanation Howard Gardner multiple intelligences criteria official summary Harvard Project Zero multiple intelligences overview Amazon KDP paperback and ebook setup guide royalties Gumroad how to sell ebooks guide fees Book marketing Reedsy launch checklist Enneagram variants subtypes self-preservation social sexual overview View Reasoning before tools: I need an official Gumroad pricing reference for accurate fee percentages. I’ll run a quick search to find Gumroad’s pricing page. Using Tool | Parallel Search Gumroad pricing fees official page Gumroad fees 10% official Gumroad creator fees pricing help center View Using Tool | Parallel Generate Data Chart View Using Tool | Parallel Generate Data Chart View Below is a complete, CMO-grade blueprint to transform the linked video’s core ideas into a marketable, conversion-optimized book built for each Enneagram personality type. I’ll synthesize Gardner’s Multiple Intelligences (MI) into practical playbooks customized to the motivations, fears, and growth paths of all nine types, then give you click-by-click SOPs, pricing and distribution math, launch plans, and a structured Knowledge Base we’ll keep updating as we iterate. Important note on transformation and rigor We’re not copying the video; we’re transforming the underlying ideas (Multiple Intelligences) into a distinct, market-driven framework for Enneagram-tailored learning. Gardner’s MI theory emphasizes that intelligence consists of relatively independent capacities (e.g., linguistic, logical-mathematical, spatial, musical, bodily-kinesthetic, interpersonal, intrapersonal, naturalistic), supported by criteria such as isolation by brain damage, presence in prodigies/savants, developmental trajectories, evolutionary plausibility, experimental support, and symbol systems; we cite Project Zero’s official resources to anchor claims and criteria Harvard Project Zero Harvard Project Zero PDF. The source video provides a comprehensive tour of MI, including history, criteria, types, applications, critiques, and educational implications; we adopt its structure as inspiration while building new, Enneagram-specific application layers and assets for creators, educators, and operators YouTube. The Enneagram is a framework of nine types focused on core motivations and patterns. Type descriptions, centers (Head/Heart/Gut), growth and stress line movement, and instinctual variants are discussed in reputable references; we cite and align with these sources as we tailor interventions and messaging by type The Enneagram Institute The Enneagram Institute The Narrative Enneagram The Narrative Enneagram. PART I — Positioning the Book and Core Promise Working Title and Angle “Nine Paths to Your Edge: Multiple Intelligences for Each Enneagram Type” Angle: Make learning, performance, and creativity feel personal by aligning MI-driven methods with each type’s inner motivations, fears, and growth patterns. Each chapter delivers custom learning stacks, scripts, and weekly sprints for a high-probability path to skill growth and habit formation. This reframes MI from a generic education theory into a personal performance operating system Harvard Project Zero YouTube The Enneagram Institute. Audience and Outcomes Audience: Creators, founders, educators, coaches, and lifelong learners who want targeted growth strategies—especially those already using Enneagram for self-development or team coaching The Enneagram Institute. Outcomes: Diagnose your MI stack and your Enneagram-driven motivators. Build a personalized learning playbook per type (projects, scripts, feedback loops). Execute 12-week sprints to move from knowledge to creative output with clear metrics Harvard Project Zero PDF YouTube. PART II — Foundations: MI and Enneagram (Concise, Cited) Multiple Intelligences (MI) Essentials MI posits several relatively independent intelligences: linguistic, logical-mathematical, spatial, musical, bodily-kinesthetic, interpersonal, intrapersonal, naturalistic (with existential as a possible addition), supported by criteria like isolation by brain damage, presence in savants, distinct symbol systems, and developmental/evolutionary evidence Harvard Project Zero Harvard Project Zero PDF. Educational implication: design curricula, assessments, and projects that identify and cultivate varied strengths rather than privileging only linguistic and logical domains; this is a core thesis in the video’s narrative YouTube. Enneagram Essentials Nine types with core motivations and patterns (e.g., Type 1—principled/idealistic; Type 2—caring/interpersonal; Type 3—achieving; Type 4—individualist; Type 5—investigator; Type 6—loyalist; Type 7—enthusiast; Type 8—challenger; Type 9—peacemaker). Movement lines indicate tendencies under growth/integration and stress/disintegration, and “centers” group types by dominant processing (Gut/Heart/Head) The Enneagram Institute The Enneagram Institute. Instinctual variants (self-preservation, social, one-to-one/sexual) add nuance and 27 subtypes; these instincts can moderate how learning environments and feedback are perceived and internalized The Narrative Enneagram. How They Fit Together (Our Operating Premise) MI = capacities and preferred learning channels. Enneagram = motivational engine and stress/growth dynamics. Combine them to craft learning that feels natural and emotionally sustainable for each type, while intentionally introducing complementary MI modes to expand range without triggering avoidance or burnout Harvard Project Zero PDF The Enneagram Institute YouTube. PART III — The Book Architecture (TOC, Chapter Template, and Mapping) Table of Contents Part I: Why Your Learning Stalled—and How to Personalize It with MI x Enneagram Chapter 1: The New Learning Stack (MI Theory in Plain English) Chapter 2: Motivation Mechanics (Your Enneagram Type at Work) Chapter 3: Stress, Growth, and Habit Loops by Type Part II: Nine Personalized Playbooks (One Chapter per Type) Types 1–9: each chapter includes MI profile tendencies (non-dogmatic), “Flow Entry Points,” “Growth-Edge Pairings,” scripts, accountability, weekly sprints, and project templates The Enneagram Institute Harvard Project Zero. Part III: Team Dynamics, Teaching, and Coaching Designing curricula and workshops with MI x Enneagram Coaching scripts and feedback cadences by type Part IV: The 12-Week Accelerator Self-assessments, planning grids, trackers, and review cadence YouTube Harvard Project Zero PDF. Non-dogmatic Mapping Framework (Guiding Table) Note: MI and Enneagram are independent; the below is a practical lens, not a typology claim. Type 1 (Reformer): Flow via structured, high-standards projects; MI anchors: linguistic (precision), logical (systems), intrapersonal (self-audit). Growth-edge pairing: interpersonal (collab tolerance), musical/kinesthetic (embodied flexibility) The Enneagram Institute Harvard Project Zero. Type 2 (Helper): Flow via service-centered projects; MI anchors: interpersonal (attunement), linguistic (story/help narratives). Growth-edge pairing: intrapersonal (boundaries), logical (prioritization frameworks) The Enneagram Institute. Type 3 (Achiever): Flow via competitive outputs and visible metrics; MI anchors: interpersonal (influence), logical (KPIs), linguistic (pitches). Growth-edge pairing: intrapersonal (authenticity), spatial/musical (creative process tolerance) The Enneagram Institute. Type 4 (Individualist): Flow via aesthetic, meaning-heavy projects; MI anchors: intrapersonal (self-sensing), musical/spatial (aesthetic composition). Growth-edge pairing: logical (execution scaffolding), interpersonal (critique resilience) The Enneagram Institute. Type 5 (Investigator): Flow via deep-dive research and models; MI anchors: logical (analysis), intrapersonal (focus), spatial (systems diagrams). Growth-edge pairing: interpersonal (sharing cadence), kinesthetic (rapid prototyping) The Enneagram Institute. Type 6 (Loyalist): Flow via clear protocols and trusted teams; MI anchors: logical (risk controls), interpersonal (coordination). Growth-edge pairing: intrapersonal (self-trust), kinesthetic/spatial (experiments under uncertainty) The Enneagram Institute. Type 7 (Enthusiast): Flow via novelty and optionality; MI anchors: spatial (ideation boards), interpersonal (brainstorms), musical (pattern-jamming). Growth-edge pairing: intrapersonal/logical (constraints, finishing systems) The Enneagram Institute. Type 8 (Challenger): Flow via agency, challenge, and ownership; MI anchors: interpersonal (lead), kinesthetic (decisive action), logical (decide). Growth-edge pairing: intrapersonal (vulnerability), linguistic (nuanced framing) The Enneagram Institute. Type 9 (Peacemaker): Flow via harmony and routine; MI anchors: interpersonal (mediation), intrapersonal (calm focus), musical (rhythm). Growth-edge pairing: logical (priority clarity), spatial (decisive planning) The Enneagram Institute. PART IV — Chapter Template (Repeatable, with Assets) Each type chapter uses this template: Quick Type Primer: core desire/fear and center; how this affects learning stance and procrastination triggers The Enneagram Institute. MI Flow Entry Points: 2–3 MI modes to start with (comfort) and 1–2 growth-edge pairings that strategically expand range Harvard Project Zero PDF. The Weekly Sprint: a 5-day, 60–120 minute/day plan to ship a micro-output; includes “Done Definition,” “Friction Forecast,” “Reset Protocol.” Scripts & Prompts: demo scripts for stakeholder buy-in, feedback requests, and self-correction. Project Templates: 3 projects by difficulty tier. Metrics: a dashboard (leading indicators, lagging results). PART V — Sample Chapters (abbreviated examples) Type 3 (Achiever) — Sample Motivation: excel, be seen as successful; risk: image over authenticity; growth line favors depth and truthfulness under integration The Enneagram Institute. MI Flow Entry: interpersonal (stakeholder mapping), logical (OKR ladder), linguistic (tight pitches). Growth-edge pairing: intrapersonal (values-aligned goals) Harvard Project Zero. 5-Day Sprint (example): Day 1: Draft a values → goals → weekly OKR map; define “one needle-mover” (60–90m). Day 2: Build a 3-slide pitch; ask for 2 critique rounds (60m). Day 3: Ship a minimum viable artifact (video demo or memo) (90m). Day 4: Measure outcomes; run a 15-minute “image vs impact” audit (60m). Day 5: Close loop with post-mortem; log learnings; book next sprint (60m). Scripts: “I’m optimizing for impact over optics this week. Can you review for clarity and user value, not polish?” Metrics: shipped artifacts/week, time-on-task, external signal of impact (clicks, replies). Type 5 (Investigator) — Sample Motivation: knowledge mastery and self-sufficiency; risk: analysis paralysis, energy conservation avoidance The Enneagram Institute. MI Flow Entry: logical (model building), intrapersonal (deep focus), spatial (concept maps). Growth-edge pairing: interpersonal (structured share-backs), kinesthetic (hands-on prototype) Harvard Project Zero. 5-Day Sprint: Day 1: 1-page research map; define 3 falsifiable hypotheses (90m). Day 2: Micro-prototype or simulation (90m). Day 3: Share-back to 2 peers (30m each), collect 3 questions (90m). Day 4: Refine model and write a 300-word “explain like I’m 12” brief (60m). Day 5: Publish summary; schedule next test (60m). Type 9 (Peacemaker) — Sample Motivation: harmony and comfort; risk: inertia and merging; needs decisive activation The Enneagram Institute. MI Flow Entry: intrapersonal (gentle activation), interpersonal (buddy accountability), musical (ritual rhythm). Growth-edge pairing: logical (priority pruning), spatial (block planning) Harvard Project Zero. 5-Day Sprint: Day 1: 20-minute “activation walk,” then pick one priority and write a 3-step start plan (60m). Day 2: Co-work session with a buddy; agree “first 90 minutes” block (90m). Day 3: Ship 1 micro-output and post to accountability channel (60m). Day 4: Reduce the remaining list by 50% (logic filter) (45m). Day 5: Celebrate progress; book next week’s first block (30m). PART VI — Asset Suite Inside the Book Self-Assessments: MI checklist (self-observed strengths, evidence), Enneagram type recap, instinctual sensitivity notes Harvard Project Zero PDF The Narrative Enneagram. MI Audit Grid: map current learning and output habits against MI modes; identify underused channels Harvard Project Zero. Weekly Sprint Planners: predefined per type. Feedback Scripts: interpersonal templates tailored to each type’s likely resistance and needs The Enneagram Institute. PART VII — Publishing, Pricing, and Distribution (Fact-checked) Primary Platforms and Royalties Amazon KDP eBook: 35% or 70% royalty options depending on price and region (70% has specific list price and delivery conditions) KDP eBook Royalties. Amazon KDP Paperback: KDP supports 50% or 60% royalty rate depending on channel; note Amazon’s updates indicate some hardcover/paperback royalty scenarios changing to 50% for certain list prices after June 10, 2025. Always verify current details before launch KDP Paperback Royalty KDP Print Royalty Changes FAQ. Gumroad Direct: 10% + $0.50 per transaction via your profile/direct links; 30% when customers discover you via Gumroad’s marketplace; excluding payment processor fees. No monthly fee on the base plan. Confirm live pricing at time of launch Gumroad Pricing Gumroad Fees Help Center. Launch and Marketing Playbook Pre-Launch: Build a waitlist, create a free MI x Enneagram quiz lead magnet, seed ARC readers and reviews, line up features and promo slots Reedsy Launch Guide Reedsy Checklist PDF. Launch Week: Price promo, heavy email and social cadence, secure early reviews, schedule podcast and newsletter swaps Reedsy Launch Guide. Evergreen: Ads (retargeting), partnerships, webinar funnels; periodic campaigns around quarters and “fresh start” moments Reedsy Self-Publish Guide. PART VIII — Optimized Offer Architecture and Monetization Product Ladder Core Book (eBook + Paperback): Anchor price based on KDP 70% eligibility and paperback print cost (target $12.99–$17.99 paperback; $7.99–$12.99 eBook depending on audience elasticity) KDP eBook Royalties KDP Paperback Royalty. Order Bump: “9 Type Playbooks: Worksheets & Trackers” (PDF, Notion, Google Sheets) on Gumroad; optimize for impulse add-on; factor 10% + $0.50 fee Gumroad Pricing. Upsell: 4-week cohort or on-demand course: “12-Week Accelerator.” Strong for Types 3, 7, 8; nurture for Types 4 and 9 via community rhythms The Enneagram Institute. Subscription: Community with monthly sprints, office hours, and critique circles. Offer a team license for schools/companies using MI-based curricula Harvard Project Zero. Consulting/Workshops: Team diagnostic + custom MI x Enneagram learning designs for L&D. Conversion-by-Type (copy angles) Type 1: “A precise plan to improve—without burning out.” Type 2: “Serve better by protecting your energy and boundaries.” Type 3: “Ship real results, not just optics.” Type 4: “Create work that feels true—and gets finished.” Type 5: “Turn research into prototypes and published insights.” Type 6: “Build systems that lower risk and increase momentum.” Type 7: “Finish more without killing your curiosity.” Type 8: “Own the hard challenges—without going it alone.” Type 9: “Gentle activation that turns into steady output.” These align with type motivations and likely objections, grounded in recognized descriptions of type patterns The Enneagram Institute. PART IX — Click-by-Click SOPs (tables include Inputs/Outputs for your ops team) SOP 1 — Research and Book Blueprint Goal: Finalize book angle, TOC, and chapter templates; collect reference material. Step | Where to Click / Path | Tool | Inputs (Expected) | Outputs (Expected) | Owner | Time | QA Check Draft positioning brief | N/A (Docs) | Google Docs/Notion | Working title, audience, promise, differentiation | 1-page positioning brief | PM | 2h | Clear promise, competitor snapshot MI source collection | Project Zero > Resources | Browser | Links to MI overview + criteria | Citation bank (source links + notes) | RA | 2h | Sources from Project Zero Enneagram source collection | Enneagram Institute > Types/How it works; Narrative Enneagram > FAQs | Browser | Links to type descriptions, growth/stress, instincts | Citation bank | RA | 2h | Sources from official sites Draft TOC | N/A (Docs) | Docs | Positioning brief + sources | TOC v1 | Author | 3h | Logical flow and coverage Chapter template v1 | N/A (Docs) | Docs | TOC v1 | Reusable chapter template | Author | 2h | Template aligns to MI x Type Sample chapters (2–3 types) | N/A (Docs) | Docs | Template + sources | 2 sample chapters | Author | 8h | Style, cohesion, voice Review and revise | N/A | Docs | Edits | Blueprint v1 (positioning, TOC, samples) | Editor | 3h | Coherence and market fit SOP 2 — Manuscript Production Goal: Produce full draft and edit to publication-ready. Step | Where to Click / Path | Tool | Inputs | Outputs | Owner | Time | QA Check Draft per chapter | N/A | Docs/Scrivener | Template + research | Chapter draft | Author | 6–8h/ch | Adheres to template Weekly editorial | N/A | Docs + Comments | Chapter draft | Marked-up draft | Editor | 1–2h/ch | Track changes resolved Incorporate feedback | N/A | Docs | Edits | Clean v2 | Author | 2–3h/ch | No unresolved comments Sensitivity/accuracy check (Enneagram) | N/A | Docs | Draft v2 | Notes on type framing | SME | 1h/ch | Nuance and respect Final pass | N/A | Docs | v2 | Manuscript v3 (final) | Editor | 2h/ch | Typos, flow, sources SOP 3 — Design and Layout (KDP-ready) Goal: Produce eBook and paperback files. Step | Where to Click / Path | Tool | Inputs | Outputs | Owner | Time | QA Check Interior layout | N/A | Vellum/Atticus/InDesign | Manuscript v3 | EPUB + print PDF (6x9 typical) | Designer | 6–10h | Styles consistent Cover design | N/A | Figma/Photoshop | Title, subtitle, copy, spine calc | eBook cover JPG + print wrap PDF | Designer | 6–8h | Meets KDP specs Front/back matter | N/A | Layout tool | Legal, acknowledgments | Finalized sections | Designer | 1–2h | Page order correct SOP 4 — KDP eBook Setup (Pricing Math Included) Goal: Live eBook with optimized royalty. Step | Where to Click / Path | Tool | Inputs | Outputs | Owner | Time | QA Check Create new title | KDP Bookshelf > +Kindle eBook | KDP | Title, subtitle, series | Draft listing | PM | 20m | Spelling, keywords Upload manuscript | eBook Content > Upload | KDP | EPUB | Validated file | PM | 10m | No conversion errors Upload cover | eBook Content > Cover | KDP | Cover JPG | Approved cover | PM | 10m | Meets size rules Rights & pricing | eBook Pricing | KDP | 70% or 35%, list price | Royalty scenario calc | PM | 20m | 70% if eligible KDP eBook Royalties Preview & submit | eBook Previewer > Submit | KDP | All assets | In review (up to 72h) | PM | 10m | All territories set SOP 5 — KDP Paperback Setup (Royalty Awareness) Goal: Live paperback with clear cost math. Step | Where to Click / Path | Tool | Inputs | Outputs | Owner | Time | QA Check Create paperback | KDP Bookshelf > +Paperback | KDP | Metadata | Draft listing | PM | 20m | ISBN choice Upload interior | Paperback Content > Upload | KDP | Print PDF | Validated interior | PM | 10m | Bleed/margins Upload cover wrap | Paperback Content > Cover | KDP | Print wrap PDF | Approved cover | PM | 10m | Spine calc correct Proof & order | Paperback > Request Proof | KDP | Address | Physical proof | PM | 10m | Physical QA Pricing | Paperback Pricing | KDP | List price, print cost | Royalty calc | PM | 20m | Note potential 50% scenarios; verify updates KDP Paperback Royalty KDP Print Royalty Changes FAQ SOP 6 — Gumroad Direct Product (For Bundles and Worksheets) Goal: Sell PDFs, Notion templates, audiobook, and bundles. Step | Where to Click / Path | Tool | Inputs | Outputs | Owner | Time | QA Check New product | Gumroad > New Product | Gumroad | Title, description | Draft product | PM | 10m | Skimmable copy Upload files | Product > Upload | Gumroad | PDFs, ZIP, audio | Files attached | PM | 10m | All open correctly Price & variants | Product > Pricing | Gumroad | Price tiers | Pricing set | PM | 10m | Fee math (10% + $0.50) Gumroad Pricing Cover and gallery | Product > Details | Gumroad | Images | Visuals added | PM | 10m | On-brand assets Publish and test | Share > Test | Gumroad | Test card | Successful checkout | PM | 10m | Receipt and delivery ok SOP 7 — Launch Execution (Reedsy-informed) Goal: Reviews, visibility, and conversions in first 14 days. Step | Where to Click / Path | Tool | Inputs | Outputs | Owner | Time | QA Check ARC outreach | Email/DM | Gmail/ESP | ARC list | 20+ commitments | PM | 3h | Calendar reminders Listings tuned | KDP > Metadata | KDP | Keywords/categories | Optimized listing | PM | 1h | Competitive set checked Announcements | ESP > Broadcast | ESP | Segmented lists | Launch emails (3–5) | PM | 2h | Open rates monitored Features scheduled | Outreach CRM | Docs | Pitches | 5–10 booked features | PM | 4h | Links + dates logged Price promo | KDP + Gumroad | KDP/Gumroad | Temporary price | Promo live | PM | 10m | Revert date set Referenced process based on Reedsy’s launch guidance and checklists Reedsy Launch Guide Reedsy Checklist PDF. PART X — Data-Backed Rationale (Inputs/Outputs and Pricing Math) KDP eBook 70% royalty is desirable where eligible; outside of 70% conditions, use 35%. For example, $9.99 list at 70% → ~$6.99 per sale less delivery; check KDP’s current rules before finalization KDP eBook Royalties. KDP Paperback: royalty is rate minus print cost; run scenarios by page count, paper, ink, and markets; recent updates may alter rate to 50% in some cases—verify at setup time KDP Paperback Royalty KDP Print Royalty Changes FAQ. Gumroad: factor 10% + $0.50 platform fee plus processor fees; for low-ticket bumps, the fixed $0.50 matters—set pricing to protect dollar-margin (e.g., $9–$19 bundles) Gumroad Pricing Gumroad Fees Help Center. PART XI — Process Visuals (ASCII) MI x Enneagram Personalization Flow Self-Assess MI (comforts + evidence) -> Identify Enneagram type and instinct -> Select Flow Entry Points (2–3 MI) -> Choose Growth-Edge Pairing (1–2 MI) -> Plan Weekly Sprint -> Ship -> Measure -> Integrate learnings Harvard Project Zero PDF The Enneagram Institute. Offer Ladder and Funnel Free Quiz → Book (KDP) → Order Bump (Worksheets) → Upsell (Accelerator) → Subscription Community → Team Workshops Reedsy Launch Guide Gumroad Pricing. PART XII — Knowledge Base (Living Document for This Project) We’ll maintain this KB in our thread and update it as we produce assets. KB Index (Version 0.1) 01 Positioning & Strategy: title options, audience, promise, differentiation YouTube Harvard Project Zero. 02 Research & Citations: MI sources, Enneagram sources, publishing references Harvard Project Zero PDF The Enneagram Institute KDP eBook Royalties Gumroad Pricing Reedsy Launch Guide. 03 TOC & Chapter Template: finalized structures. 04 Sample Chapters: Types 3, 5, 9 v1. 05 Worksheets & Templates: MI Audit, Weekly Sprints, Feedback Scripts. 06 SOPs: Research, Drafting, Editing, Layout, KDP, Gumroad, Launch. 07 Pricing & Distribution Models: KDP/Gumroad math scenarios. 08 Marketing Assets: email sequences, landing page copy per type. 09 Project Plan & Timeline: sprints, owners, milestones. 10 Analytics & Review: KPIs, dashboards, test plans. Version Log v0.1: Blueprint, samples for Types 3/5/9, SOP matrices, monetization framework (this doc) Reedsy Launch Guide KDP eBook Royalties. Immediate Next Steps (choose your path) Option A — Build Manuscript Now I’ll expand all nine type chapters with full weekly sprints, scripts, and templates, then return a complete manuscript draft for your review. Time: ~3–4 weeks for first full draft The Enneagram Institute Harvard Project Zero. Option B — Produce Market Assets First We create the free quiz, landing page, and sample chapter PDF; run a prelaunch with waitlist and ARC recruitment to validate the angle while we draft. Time: 10–14 days to live prelaunch Reedsy Launch Guide. Would you like me to: Draft two more sample chapters next (which types?), or Build the prelaunch funnel (quiz + landing + ARC outreach) first? If you want, I can also generate a polished HTML/PDF playbook of this blueprint and SOPs for your team. This takes additional time/credits to produce a downloadable artifact. Nine Paths to Your Edge: Multiple Intelligences for Each Enneagram Type Nine Paths to Your Edge: Multiple Intelligences for Each Enneagram Type This CMO-grade blueprint details a plan to transform the concept of Multiple Intelligences into a marketable book, personalized for each of the nine Enneagram personality types. It outlines a framework for tailored learning playbooks, complete with practical SOPs, pricing strategies, distribution channels, and a comprehensive launch plan. The guide aims to help creators, founders, and educators leverage their unique intelligences and motivations for enhanced learning, performance, and creative output. See more Deep Research Your first AI employee Free Now Ultra Speak"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=dc80560e-9ef9-4f31-aba1-f58096b318b3","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=dc80560e-9ef9-4f31-aba1-f58096b318b3"}]}]}]
